{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2360 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2360 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C2360","pos":[597,617]},{"content":"initialization of 'identifier' is skipped by 'case' label","pos":[618,675]},{"content":"The initialization of <ph id=\"ph1\">`identifier`</ph> can be skipped in a <ph id=\"ph2\">`switch`</ph> statement.","pos":[682,756],"source":"The initialization of `identifier` can be skipped in a `switch` statement."},{"content":"You cannot jump past a declaration with an initializer unless the declaration is enclosed in a block.","pos":[757,858]},{"content":"(Unless it is declared within a block, the variable is within scope until the end of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`switch`</ph> statement.)","pos":[859,968],"source":" (Unless it is declared within a block, the variable is within scope until the end of the `switch` statement.)"},{"content":"The following sample generates C2360:","pos":[975,1012]},{"content":"Possible resolution:","pos":[1211,1231]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2360 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2360\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2360\"\nms.assetid: 51bfd2ee-8108-4777-aa93-148b9cebfa83\ncaps.latest.revision: 8\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2360\ninitialization of 'identifier' is skipped by 'case' label  \n  \n The initialization of `identifier` can be skipped in a `switch` statement. You cannot jump past a declaration with an initializer unless the declaration is enclosed in a block. (Unless it is declared within a block, the variable is within scope until the end of the `switch` statement.)  \n  \n The following sample generates C2360:  \n  \n```  \n// C2360.cpp  \nint main() {  \n   int x = 0;  \n   switch ( x ) {  \n   case 0 :  \n      int i = 1;  \n      { int j = 1; }  \n   case 1 :   // C2360  \n      int k = 1;  \n   }  \n}  \n```  \n  \n Possible resolution:  \n  \n```  \n// C2360b.cpp  \nint main() {  \n   int x = 0;  \n   switch ( x ) {  \n   case 0 :  \n      { int j = 1; int i = 1;}  \n   case 1 :  \n      int k = 1;  \n   }  \n}  \n```"}